### Data Plan (Schemas, Migrations, Privacy/Retention)

- Goal(s): Define data modeling, migration, privacy classification, retention.

### Assumptions
- PII is present; regional constraints possible.

### Alternatives
- Ad-hoc migrations; no DPIA (non-compliant).

### Risks & Mitigations
- Data loss (L×H): Backups, migration dry-runs.
- Privacy breach (L×H): Data minimization; access controls.

### Dependencies
- Schema tooling, migration system, DPIA templates.

### Schemas & Migrations
- Versioned schemas; up/down migrations; blue/green or expand-contract.

### Privacy & Retention
- Classify PII/PHI; retention by category; deletion workflows; DSR handling.

### Trigger → Rule → File(s)/Output mapping

| Trigger | Rules | Files/Outputs | Gates |
|---|---|---|---|
| data schema | `F5-data-ml` | This plan + schema repo | Migration plan reviewed |
| security | `F8-security` | `security-plan.md` | Access controls validated |

### Success Metrics
- Zero prod data-loss incidents; >95% access compliance.

### Next Steps
- Author initial ERD; define retention matrix and DSR SOP.
